### Auth — login, refresh, guard.
### Select environment "local" (8080) or "local-8081" in the run toolbar.
### Demo user (seeded): demo / password123.

### Login → captures accessToken + refreshToken for every other .http file
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "demo",
  "password": "password123"
}

> {%
    client.test("login ok", function () {
        client.assert(response.status === 200, "expected 200");
    });
    client.global.set("token", response.body.accessToken);
    client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.refreshToken);
%}

### Refresh tokens (rotation: both tokens are re-issued)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("token", response.body.accessToken);
    client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.refreshToken);
%}

### Wrong password → 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "demo",
  "password": "wrong-password"
}

### No token on a protected endpoint → 401
GET {{baseUrl}}/accounts
